data.description: You’ll love to entertain guests and marvel at the tranquility of water views at this one-of-a-kind classic Key West home on Philippi Creek Bayou. Enter through the mahogany doors and you will be thrilled to see soaring cathedral ceilings allowing natural light and life into the home. The home offers expansive water views from most rooms. It will be easy to relax on the outside deck facing beautiful sunsets. Enjoy the Key West coral fireplace on cooler nights and marvel at the stunning natural maple hardwood floors found throughout the home. The chef’s kitchen will inspire the family cook to host events for every occasion with stainless appliances, stainless chef's cooking area and quartz countertops that enhance the marine feel in this home. The wrap-around bar is sure to promote warm memories while cooking and entertaining. The enormous primary suite features its private balcony with water view, charming gas fireplace and bay windows. En-suite bath features vanities and spa tub to relax in after the beach. There is dedicated office space for those who work from home or want a private study area for the kids. The upper level features four bedrooms, a balcony and two full baths. The lower level features a huge entertaining area and pool bath which is ideal for hosting large gatherings. The private open pool area sits at the edge of the water with long peaceful views of the canal. The fun does not end on dry land. At the water, there is a kayak launch, jet ski floats and a new composite boat dock with a 13,000-pound lift to fulfill your captain’s or angler’s dreams. Just minutes to Philippi Shores Elementary and Riverview High School makes this home ideal for the growing family that loves the outdoors. A treasured Suncoast oasis to live out waterfront wishes, this private unique estate is everything you’ve wanted and more.
